          h3 Command Line
          p <span class="orange">1 </span> To run gitignore.io from your command line you need an active internet connection an environment function.  You need to add a function to your environment that lets you access the gitignore.io API.
          blockquote
            h5.normal Linux
          h5 #!/bin/bash
          pre $ echo "function gi() { curl http://gitignore.io/api/\$@ ;}"  >> ~/.bashrc && source ~/.bashrc
          blockquote
            h5.normal OSX
          h5 #!/bin/bash
          pre $ echo "function gi() { curl http://gitignore.io/api/\$@ ;}"  >> ~/.bash_profile && source ~/.bash_profile
          h5 #!/bin/zsh
          pre $ echo "function gi() { curl http://gitignore.io/api/$@ ;}"  >> ~/.zshrc && . ~/.zshrc
          p <span class="orange">2 </span> After the function is created, the <strong>gi</strong> command will give you command line access to the gitingore.io API.
          blockquote
            h5.normal Show ouput on the command line
          pre $ gi linux,java
            | # Generated by http://gitignore.io
            | &nbsp;
            | ### Linux ###
            | .*
            | !.gitignore
            | *~
            | &nbsp;
            | ### Java ###
            | *.class
            | &nbsp;
            | # Package Files #
            | *.jar
            | *.war
            | *.ear
          blockquote
            h5.normal Append Operating System and IDE settings to global .gitignore
          pre $ gi linux,eclipse >> ~/.gitignore
          blockquote
            h5.normal Append programming languages to your project .gitignore file
          pre $ gi java,python >> .gitignore
